title: Inspector_Lewis_S08E02_-_The_Lions_of_Nemea.m4v
description: This is the complete second episode of the eighth series of Inspector Lewis. An American classical studies graduate student (female) at Oxford is murdered. Both a classics scholar and an astronomy professor seem to be connected to the case. Another classics professor, her optometrist husband, and their seemingly healthy but seriously ill daughter are also in the mix. The wife of the astronomy professor is the sister of the classics professor and she (the classics prof) almost becomes attached to Hathaway in the manner that occurred in almost every episode of Morse. Oh, and there is a drug dealer. You might want to lookup Fanconi anemia on Wikipedia and good luck
